pan class=title> Crystalized Pumice stone question</span><hr size=1> I got this email posing some questions about pumice... hope someone can help him out.  Thanks!<br>
------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I heard it is dropped by Mobs, where i do not know, but it is suppose to be the unnerfed version<br>
of the pumice stone. is this true? i haven't heard people talking about this. Is it because it doesn't exist or the mob that drops it is just to darn hard to farm? Or it is a camped spawn mob? Also it was stated in the duel section that the current pumice stone cannot nullify your opponent, only yourself. Is that true also? <br>
<br>
I have won duel's without having to use a pumice stone simply because i follow the dueling guide rules:<br>
1. do not initiate a duel and do not accept until its in my favor.<br>
2. i run around getting buffs all over the place. Usually the Sow and HP and Mr buffs towards the back. With other kind of buffs in front. Like Dex, agi, char, int, clarity.. just so i do not get the buffs i need to win to be<br>
canceled. In all reality they only get to defuff you a couple maybe few times until I can get into range and get into the grove of CoD'n the bastard till<br>
they drop. ;)<br>
<br>
I have no problems with melee'r except for the SK. Damm that HT. But with the HP buffs from high level cleric and regen from a druid and with chloroplast and SLN .. Im pretty hard to beat. I usually take down challengers 5-7 levels above me.<br>
<br>
I have yet to use poisons as im not high enough to use them im only level 18, but i guess i can get  the one from Tox in FP now and start applying poisons. Just to try it out. Oh wait i did use poison in a recent duel with a fighter, he went down pretty quick as we were both of same level.<br>
I kited him with Sow and a bow and arrow... fletched oak bow.. so i was hitting for 18-20 points a shot... and he had the snake poison on him. Someone gave me a sample to try out. hehe forgot about that one. <br>
<br>
Well back to the original question, Crystalized pumice? where is it?<br>
<br>
